id: pm-92if
title: "CodeFactor remediation: drive code quality from A to A+ (zero outstanding findings)"
description: "Track and eliminate every CodeFactor finding so the repository reaches the best attainable rating with no outstanding issues.\n\n## Source\n\n- CodeFactor overview: https://www.codefactor.io/repository/github/unbraind/pm-cli/overview/main\n- Issues: https://www.codefactor.io/repository/github/unbraind/pm-cli/issues/main\n- Files by rating: https://www.codefactor.io/repository/github/unbraind/pm-cli/files/main?grid-column=Rating&grid-dir=0\n\nCodeFactor was wired up alongside Codecov in commit `d42ae71b` (README badge + `.codefactor.yml` scoping analysis to hand-authored source, excluding `.agents/**`, `CHANGELOG.md`, `PRD.md`, `pnpm-lock.yaml`).\n\n## Snapshot (captured 2026-06-26)\n\n- Overall grade: **A** (98.7% A-rated files, 1.0% B, 0.3% C)\n- Files analyzed: 601 · Active branch: main\n- **Total outstanding issues: 261**\n\n| Category | Count | Severity / rule split |\n|---|---|---|\n| Complexity | 152 | Critical 3 · High 7 · Moderate 142 |\n| Maintainability | 89 | `no-useless-fallback-in-spread` 57 · unsafe optional chaining 25 · `no-thenable` 4 · `no-useless-spread` 2 · `no-useless-length-check` 1 |\n| Duplication | 20 | Critical 2 · Major 3 · Minor 15 |\n\n## Hotspot files (lowest-rated)\n\n1. `src/sdk/cli-contracts.ts` (B) — includes the `no-thenable` findings (`then:` keys at lines 2483, 2493)\n2. `tests/unit/commands/create-command.spec.ts` (C)\n3. `tests/unit/commands/update-command.spec.ts` (B)\n4. `src/cli/commands/search.ts` (B)\n5. `src/cli/main.ts` (B)\n\n## Approach\n\nChild items break the work down by category and rule. Order of attack:\n1. Maintainability — mechanical, low-risk, auto-fixable ESLint rules (fastest grade wins).\n2. Duplication — extract shared helpers (Critical/Major first).\n3. Complexity — refactor the worst functions (Critical/High first), then chip away at Moderate.\n4. Stand up local lint/quality parity so the team can reach zero and prevent regressions.\n\nNOTE: CodeFactor analyzes its own snapshot; `.agents/**` (the git-native work-item store, where these very items live), `CHANGELOG.md`, `PRD.md`, and the lockfile are excluded by `.codefactor.yml`, so these tracking items do not themselves add findings."
type: Epic
status: in_progress
priority: 2
tags[3]: code-quality,codefactor,tech-debt
created_at: "2026-06-26T13:29:14.359Z"
updated_at: "2026-06-28T06:54:50.367Z"
assignee: codex-gpt5
author: claude-code-agent
acceptance_criteria: "CodeFactor overall repository grade reaches A+ (or the highest attainable) on branch main; CodeFactor reports 0 outstanding issues across Complexity, Maintainability, and Duplication; local lint/quality parity tooling exists so findings can be reproduced and kept at zero (no regressions on new PRs)."
