  "2026-06-27T22:20:22.418Z",codex-gpt5,"Review fix evidence for PR #391: addressed the Gemini Code Assist lifecycle finding by changing generated imperative and declarative package starter tests to use createExtensionTestHarness-bound assert/run helpers consistently and to call await ext.deactivate() in finally blocks for every activation-bearing sample. Verification after the fix: node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/unit/extensions/extension-scaffold-define-guidance.spec.ts passed 26/26; node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/unit/extensions/extension-command.spec.ts passed 111/111; pnpm typecheck passed; pnpm quality:static passed; pnpm lint passed; git diff --check passed; pnpm build passed; node scripts/run-tests.mjs coverage passed 256 files / 5138 tests with 100% statements, 100% branches, 100% functions, 100% lines; rebuilt manual temp smoke at /tmp/tmp.fUHNts0IWX passed pm init, package init, install, package doctor ok with zero warnings, starter command JSON invocation, generated package npm run typecheck, and generated package npm test 2/2; pnpm contracts:check passed; pnpm security:scan reported no credential-like secrets; pnpm audit --audit-level moderate reported no known vulnerabilities; node scripts/release/sentry-telemetry-gate.mjs --json --telemetry-mode best-effort passed with Sentry critical=0 high=0 total=0 and telemetry finish_error_rate_pct=0.75 failures_without_error_code_rows=0; pnpm changelog:pm:check used pm-changelog 2026.6.27 and left CHANGELOG.md unchanged at item_count=1363; pm test pm-92if --run --progress passed all 10 linked tests."
  "2026-06-27T22:42:32.701Z",codex-gpt5,"Second review fix evidence for PR #391: addressed current-head Gemini, CodeRabbit, and cubic feedback by making generated starter tests assert ext.deactivate() results with assertExtensionDeactivated(teardown) at the end of successful try blocks, while keeping finally blocks for fallback cleanup only via if (!deactivated) await ext.deactivate(); this avoids masking primary assertion failures while still detecting teardown regressions. Also tightened scaffold tests to assert the generated try/finally cleanup shape and teardown assertion. Verification after this fix: node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/unit/extensions/extension-command.spec.ts passed 111/111; node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/unit/extensions/extension-scaffold-define-guidance.spec.ts passed 26/26; pnpm typecheck passed; pnpm lint passed; pnpm quality:static passed; git diff --check passed; node scripts/run-tests.mjs coverage passed 256 files / 5138 tests with 100% statements, 100% branches, 100% functions, and 100% lines; rebuilt manual temp smoke at /tmp/tmp.vWMdOkZsal passed pm init, package init, install, package doctor ok with zero warnings, starter command JSON invocation, generated package npm run typecheck, and generated package npm test 2/2; pnpm contracts:check passed; pnpm security:scan reported no credential-like secrets; pnpm audit --audit-level moderate reported no known vulnerabilities; Sentry/telemetry gate passed with critical=0 high=0 total=0 and telemetry finish_error_rate_pct=0.75 failures_without_error_code_rows=0; pnpm changelog:pm:check used pm-changelog 2026.6.27 and left CHANGELOG.md unchanged at item_count=1363; pm test pm-92if --run --progress passed all 10 linked tests."
  "2026-06-27T23:02:42.261Z",codex-gpt5,"Third PR #391 review fix evidence: addressed current-head Gemini and cubic feedback by wrapping generated fallback ext.deactivate() cleanup calls in try/catch so cleanup cannot mask the primary assertion or teardown failure. Added scaffold expectations for let deactivated = false, assertExtensionDeactivated(teardown), guarded fallback cleanup, and catch {} in command, non-command, and declarative starter test templates. Verification after this fix: pnpm build; focused extension-command and extension-scaffold tests; pnpm typecheck; git diff --check; pnpm quality:static; pnpm contracts:check; pnpm security:scan; pnpm lint; full coverage 256 files / 5138 tests / 100% statements, branches, functions, lines; pnpm audit --audit-level moderate no known vulnerabilities; sentry telemetry gate ok with 0 critical/high Sentry issues and telemetry finish error rate 0.75%; pnpm changelog:pm:check with pm-changelog 2026.6.27 unchanged CHANGELOG; manual temp smoke at /tmp/tmp.wdDfYPF1gm covered init, package init, install, package doctor ok with 0 warnings, starter command ping, generated package typecheck, and generated package tests; pm test pm-92if --run --progress passed all 10 linked tests."
  "2026-06-28T06:26:52.626Z",codex-gpt5,"Implementation start 2026-06-28: continuing the active CodeFactor/SDK quality lane after duplicate-safe status-all orientation, GitHub PR/issue/security sweep, pnpm audit, lint/typecheck/security/static gates, and open-item triage. Scope is public source-quality cleanup: reduce duplicated SDK/CLI option-contract helpers, single-source custom type default-folder derivation, and remove unnecessary Sentry test any typings without changing runtime behavior."
  "2026-06-28T06:54:50.367Z",codex-gpt5,"Evidence 2026-06-28: implemented public source-quality cleanup by single-sourcing custom item default-folder derivation through type-registry, deduplicating SDK tool option contract slices without changing the contract snapshot, and replacing unnecessary Sentry test any payload typings. Verification passed: pnpm build; focused source-quality tests node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/unit/core/store/store-paths.spec.ts tests/unit/core/sentry/sentry-helpers.spec.ts tests/unit/commands/contracts-command.spec.ts tests/unit/sdk/sdk-index.spec.ts (4 files / 197 tests); node scripts/run-tests.mjs coverage (256 files / 5138 tests / 100% statements, branches, functions, and lines); pnpm typecheck; pnpm lint; pnpm quality:static (static gate passed, duplicate chunks now 26 / 809 duplicated TS lines); pnpm contracts:check; pnpm security:scan; pnpm audit --audit-level moderate; git diff --check. pm test pm-92if --run --progress passed the 14 linked sandbox-compatible commands after removing repo-wide coverage and contracts snapshot from linked execution because pm test schema-context sandbox changes their runtime context; both direct gates passed on the current working tree. Manual temp smoke at /tmp/tmp.TlcR1qJCP0/work/.agents/pm passed init, research type preset, schema add-type research-note, Task and research-note create/list, health, validate, and verified the custom item stored under research-notes/. GitHub sweep found no open PRs, no Dependabot/code-scanning/secret-scanning alerts, pnpm audit clean, and issue #374 still externally blocked on missing RELEASE_PAT. Changelog check used pm-changelog 2026.6.27 and CHANGELOG.md remained unchanged (item_count=1363); package doctor deep ok with zero warnings; health summary ok; history drift ok with existing validate_resolution_missing_fields:258 backlog; Sentry/telemetry gate ok with critical=0 high=0 telemetry finish_error_rate_pct=0.76 and failures_without_error_code_rows=0."
